@tomislacker as far as I know, that assumption is correct, rules are always given back in order and are 1-indexed from the viewpoint of iptables.

Unfortunately, python-iptables could only add rule number information to the rule objects via quite some extra runtime overhead (always traversing all the rules in the chain to make sure numbers are not off, e.g. when rules have been added/removed in another process).

Instead, I'd opt for adding more documentation on how rules are numbered. Feel free to send a PR, not sure when I'll have the time to do it myself.

