You can create a custom middleware to catch these exceptions. Like this one:


```
from social.apps.django_app.middleware import SocialAuthExceptionMiddleware
from social.exceptions import AuthCanceled
from django.shortcuts import redirect, render

class SocialAuthExceptionMiddleware(SocialAuthExceptionMiddleware):
    """
    Handles login error exception generated by social authentication app
    """
    def process_exception(self, request, exception):
        if type(exception) == AuthCanceled:
            return render(request, 'login_error.html', {'error_message': exception})
        else:
            raise exception
```

This one catches exceptions on cancelled Authentications. You can edit and create one that fits your needs.

