Again, we expect each executor to host only one TF node.  And from this, it appears that you have two physical hosts (worker1, worker2), but only two executor processes (ppid=7751, 25378) that ran the reserve tasks.  Are you sure that you're actually getting the 4 executors that you requested?  Perhaps you need to reduce `--executor-memory` to "fit" more executors onto the same host (e.g. 600M for 2 executors => 300M for 4 executors)?

Note: I've seen cases where YARN can actually return fewer than requested hosts, and Spark will attempt to proceed...

