Another work-around:

```python
class X(HasTraits):

    a = Int(1)
    b = Int(10)
    c = Int(100)

    @observe("a", "b", "c")
    def abc_increase(self, change, seen=[]):
        if change.name not in seen:
            seen.append(change.name)
        if len(seen) == 3 and not self.a < self.b < self.c:
            raise ValueError("%s < %s < %s is not true" % (self.a, self.b, self.c))
```

